acupressure.desc: Raises a random stat by 2 stages as long as the stat is not already at stage 6. The user can choose to use this move on itself or an ally. Fails if no stat stage can be raised or if the user or ally has a substitute.
acupressure.name: Acupressure
acupressure.shortDesc: Raises a random stat of the user or an ally by 2.

aromatherapy.desc: Every Pokemon in the user's party is cured of its non-volatile status condition.
aromatherapy.name: Aromatherapy
aromatherapy.shortDesc: Cures the user's party of all status conditions.

aquaring.name: Aqua Ring
aquaring.desc: The user has 1/16 of its maximum HP, rounded down, restored at the end of each turn while it remains active. If Big Root is held by the user, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded half down. If the user uses Baton Pass, the replacement will receive the healing effect.
aquaring.shortDesc: User recovers 1/16 max HP per turn.

beatup.desc: Deals typeless damage. Hits one time for the user and one time for each unfainted Pokemon without a non-volatile status condition in the user's party. For each hit, the damage formula uses the participating Pokemon's base Attack as the Attack stat, the target's base Defense as the Defense stat, and ignores stat stages and other effects that modify Attack or Defense; each hit is considered to come from the user.
beatup.name: Beat Up
beatup.shortDesc: All healthy allies aid in damaging the target.

bide.desc: The user spends two turns locked into this move and then, on the second turn after using this move, the user attacks the last Pokemon that hit it, inflicting double the damage in HP it lost to attacks during the two turns. If the last Pokemon that hit it is no longer active, the user attacks a random opposing Pokemon instead. If the user is prevented from moving during this move's use, the effect ends. This move does not check accuracy and ignores type immunity.
bide.name: Bide
bide.shortDesc: Waits 2 turns; deals double the damage taken.

bind.desc: Prevents the target from switching for two to five turns (always five turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/16 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-turn. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Rapid Spin or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
bind.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 2-5 turns.
bind.name: Bind

bonerush.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
bonerush.name: Bone Rush

bravebird.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/3 the HP lost by the target, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
bravebird.name: Brave Bird

bulletseed.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
bulletseed.name: Bullet Seed

camouflage.desc: The user's type changes based on the battle terrain. Normal type on the regular Wi-Fi terrain. Fails if the user has the Multitype Ability or if the type is one of the user's current types.
camouflage.shortDesc: Changes user's type based on terrain. (Normal)
camouflage.name: Camouflage

chatter.desc: Has an X% chance to confuse the target, where X is 0 unless the user is a Chatot that hasn't Transformed. If the user is a Chatot, X is 1, 11, or 31 depending on the volume of Chatot's recorded cry, if any; 1 for no recording or low volume, 11 for medium volume, and 31 for high volume.
chatter.shortDesc: For Chatot, 31% chance to confuse the target.
chatter.name: Chatter

clamp.desc: Prevents the target from switching for two to five turns (always five turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/16 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-turn. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Rapid Spin or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
clamp.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 2-5 turns.
clamp.name: Clamp

conversion.desc: The user's type changes to match the original type of one of its known moves besides this move and Curse, at random, but not either of its current types. Fails if the user cannot change its type, or if this move would only be able to select one of the user's current types.
conversion.shortDesc: Changes user's type to match a known move.
conversion.name: Conversion

cottonspore.name: Cotton Spore
cottonspore.desc: Lowers the target's Speed by 2 stages.

covet.desc: If this attack was successful and the user has not fainted, it steals the target's held item if the user is not holding one. The target's item is not stolen if it is a Mail or Griseous Orb, or if the target has the Multitype Ability. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle.
covet.name: Covet
covet.shortDesc: If the user has no item, it steals the target's.

crabhammer.name: Crabhammer
crabhammer.desc: Has a higher chance for a critical hit.

crushgrip.desc: Power is equal to 120 * (target's current HP / target's maximum HP) + 1, rounded down.
crushgrip.name: Crush Grip
crushgrip.shortDesc: More power the more HP the target has left.

curse.desc: If the user is not a Ghost type, lowers the user's Speed by 1 stage and raises the user's Attack and Defense by 1 stage. If the user is a Ghost type, the user loses 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded down and even if it would cause fainting, in exchange for the target losing 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn while it is active. If the target uses Baton Pass, the replacement will continue to be affected. Fails if there is no target or if the target is already affected or has a substitute.
curse.name: Curse
curse.shortDesc: Curses if Ghost, else -1 Spe, +1 Atk, +1 Def.

defog.desc: Lowers the target's evasiveness by 1 stage. If this move is successful and whether or not the target's evasiveness was affected, the effects of Reflect, Light Screen, Safeguard, Mist, Spikes, Toxic Spikes, and Stealth Rock end for the target's side. Ignores a target's substitute, although a substitute will still block the lowering of evasiveness.
defog.name: Defog

detect.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and doubles each time this move is successfully used, up to a maximum of 8. X resets to 1 if this move fails or if the user's last move used is not Detect, Endure, or Protect. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
detect.name: Detect
detect.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

disable.desc: For 4 to 7 turns, the target's last move used becomes disabled. Fails if one of the target's moves is already disabled, if the target has not made a move, if the target no longer knows the move, or if the move has 0 PP.
disable.shortDesc: For 4-7 turns, disables the target's last move.
disable.name: Disable

doomdesire.desc: Deals typeless damage that cannot be a critical hit two turns after this move is used. Damage is calculated against the target on use, and at the end of the final turn that damage is dealt to the Pokemon at the position the original target had at the time. Fails if this move or Future Sight is already in effect for the target's position.
doomdesire.name: Doom Desire
doomdesire.shortDesc: Hits two turns after being used.

doubleedge.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/3 the HP lost by the target, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
doubleedge.name: Double-Edge

drainpunch.desc: The user recovers 1/2 the HP lost by the target, rounded down. If Big Root is held by the user, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded down.
drainpunch.name: Drain Punch
drainpunch.shortDesc: User recovers 50% of the damage dealt.

dreameater.desc: The target is unaffected by this move unless it is asleep and does not have a substitute. The user recovers 1/2 the HP lost by the target, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP. If Big Root is held by the user, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded down.
dreameater.name: Dream Eater
dreameater.shortDesc: User gains 1/2 HP inflicted. Sleeping target only.

embargo.name: Embargo
embargo.desc: For 5 turns, the target's held item has no effect. An item's effect of causing forme changes is unaffected, but any other effects from such items are negated. During the effect, Fling and Natural Gift are prevented from being used by the target. Items thrown at the target with Fling will still activate for it. If the target uses Baton Pass, the replacement will remain unable to use items.
embargo.shortDesc: For 5 turns, the target's item has no effect.

encore.desc: For 4 to 8 turns, the target is forced to repeat its last move used. If the affected move runs out of PP, the effect ends. Fails if the target is already under this effect, if it has not made a move, if the move has 0 PP, or if the move is Encore, Mimic, Mirror Move, Sketch, Struggle, or Transform.
encore.shortDesc: The target repeats its last move for 4-8 turns.
encore.name: Encore

endeavor.name: Endeavor
endeavor.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to (target's current HP - user's current HP). The target is unaffected if its current HP is less than or equal to the user's current HP.
endeavor.shortDesc: Lowers the target's HP to the user's HP.

fakeout.name: Fake Out
fakeout.desc: Has a 100% chance to make the target flinch. Fails unless it is the user's first turn on the field.
fakeout.shortDesc: Hits first. First turn out only. 100% flinch chance.

feint.desc: Fails unless the target is using Detect or Protect. If this move is successful, it breaks through the target's Detect or Protect for this turn, allowing other Pokemon to attack the target normally.
feint.shortDesc: Breaks protection. Fails if target is not protecting.
feint.name: Feint

firespin.desc: Prevents the target from switching for two to five turns (always five turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/16 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-turn. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Rapid Spin or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
firespin.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 2-5 turns.
firespin.name: Fire Spin

flail.desc: The power of this move is 20 if X is 43 to 48, 40 if X is 22 to 42, 80 if X is 13 to 21, 100 if X is 6 to 12, 150 if X is 2 to 5, and 200 if X is 0 or 1, where X is equal to (user's current HP * 64 / user's maximum HP), rounded down.
flail.name: Flail
flail.shortDesc: More power the less HP the user has left.

flareblitz.desc: Has a 10% chance to burn the target. If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/3 the HP lost by the target, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
flareblitz.shortDesc: Has 1/3 recoil. 10% chance to burn. Thaws user.
flareblitz.name: Flare Blitz

focuspunch.desc: The user loses its focus and does nothing if it is hit by a damaging attack this turn before it can execute the move, but it still loses PP.
focuspunch.name: Focus Punch
focuspunch.shortDesc: Fails if the user takes damage before it hits.

foresight.desc: As long as the target remains active, its evasiveness stat stage is ignored during accuracy checks against it if it is greater than 0, and Normal- and Fighting-type attacks can hit the target if it is a Ghost type.
foresight.name: Foresight
foresight.shortDesc: Fighting, Normal hit Ghost. Evasiveness ignored.

furycutter.name: Fury Cutter
furycutter.desc: Power doubles with each successful hit, up to a maximum of 160 power. The power is reset if this move misses or another move is used.
furycutter.shortDesc: Power doubles with each hit, up to 160.

futuresight.desc: Deals typeless damage that cannot be a critical hit two turns after this move is used. Damage is calculated against the target on use, and at the end of the final turn that damage is dealt to the Pokemon at the position the original target had at the time. Fails if this move or Doom Desire is already in effect for the target's position.
futuresight.name: Future Sight
futuresight.shortDesc: Hits two turns after being used.

gigadrain.desc: The user recovers 1/2 the HP lost by the target, rounded down. If Big Root is held by the user, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded down.
gigadrain.name: Giga Drain
gigadrain.shortDesc: User recovers 50% of the damage dealt.

gravity.desc: For 5 turns, the evasiveness of all active Pokemon is multiplied by 0.6. At the time of use, Bounce, Fly, and Magnet Rise end immediately for all active Pokemon. During the effect, Bounce, Fly, High Jump Kick, Jump Kick, Magnet Rise, and Splash are prevented from being used by all active Pokemon. Ground-type attacks, Spikes, Toxic Spikes, and the Arena Trap Ability can affect Flying types or Pokemon with the Levitate Ability. Fails if this move is already in effect.
gravity.name: Gravity

growth.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack by 1 stage.
growth.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk by 1.
growth.name: Growth

healbell.desc: Every Pokemon in the user's party is cured of its non-volatile status condition. Pokemon with the Soundproof Ability are not cured.
healbell.name: Heal Bell
healbell.shortDesc: Cures the user's party of all status conditions.

healblock.desc: For 5 turns, the target is prevented from restoring any HP as long as it remains active. During the effect, healing moves are unusable, move effects that grant healing will not heal, but Abilities and items will continue to heal the user. If an affected Pokemon uses Baton Pass, the replacement will remain under the effect. Pain Split is unaffected.
healblock.name: Heal Block
healblock.shortDesc: For 5 turns, the foe(s) is prevented from healing.

healingwish.desc: The user faints and the Pokemon brought out to replace it has its HP fully restored along with having any non-volatile status condition cured. The new Pokemon is sent out immediately and the healing happens after hazards take effect. Fails if the user is the last unfainted Pokemon in its party.
healingwish.shortDesc: User faints. Replacement is fully healed.
healingwish.name: Healing Wish

highjumpkick.desc: If this attack is not successful, the user loses HP equal to half the target's maximum HP if the target was immune, rounded down, otherwise half of the damage the target would have taken, rounded down, but no less than 1 HP and no more than half of the target's maximum HP, as crash damage. Pokemon with the Magic Guard Ability are unaffected by crash damage.
highjumpkick.shortDesc: If miss, user takes 1/2 damage it would've dealt.
highjumpkick.name: High Jump Kick

iciclespear.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
iciclespear.name: Icicle Spear

imprison.desc: The user prevents all opposing Pokemon from using any moves that the user also knows as long as the user remains active. Fails if no opposing Pokemon know any of the user's moves.
imprison.name: Imprison
imprison.shortDesc: No foe can use any move known by the user.

ingrain.desc: The user has 1/16 of its maximum HP restored at the end of each turn, but it is prevented from switching out and other Pokemon cannot force the user to switch out. The user can still switch out if it uses Baton Pass or U-turn. If the user leaves the field using Baton Pass, the replacement will remain trapped and still receive the healing effect. During the effect, the user can be hit normally by Ground-type attacks and be affected by Spikes and Toxic Spikes, even if the user is a Flying type or has the Levitate Ability.
ingrain.name: Ingrain
ingrain.shortDesc: Traps/grounds user; heals 1/16 max HP per turn.

jumpkick.desc: If this attack is not successful, the user loses HP equal to half the target's maximum HP if the target was immune, rounded down, otherwise half of the damage the target would have taken, rounded down, but no less than 1 HP and no more than half of the target's maximum HP, as crash damage. Pokemon with the Magic Guard Ability are unaffected by crash damage.
jumpkick.shortDesc: If miss, user takes 1/2 damage it would've dealt.
jumpkick.name: Jump Kick

knockoff.desc: The target's held item is lost for the rest of the battle, unless the item is a Griseous Orb or the target has the Multitype or Sticky Hold Abilities. During the effect, the target cannot obtain a new item by any means.
knockoff.shortDesc: Target's item is lost and it cannot obtain another.
knockoff.name: Knock Off

lastresort.name: Last Resort
lastresort.desc: This move fails unless the user knows this move and at least one other move, and has used all the other moves it knows at least once each since it became active or Transformed.
lastresort.shortDesc: Fails unless each known move has been used.

leechseed.desc: The Pokemon at the user's position steals 1/8 of the target's maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn. If Big Root is held by the recipient, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded half down. If the target uses Baton Pass, the replacement will continue being leeched. If the target switches out or uses Rapid Spin successfully, the effect ends. Grass-type Pokemon are immune to this move on use, but not its effect.
leechseed.name: Leech Seed
leechseed.shortDesc: 1/8 of target's HP is restored to user every turn.

lightscreen.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 1/2 damage from special attacks, or 2/3 damage if there are multiple active Pokemon on the user's side. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
lightscreen.name: Light Screen
lightscreen.shortDesc: For 5 turns, special damage to allies is halved.

lockon.desc: Until the end of the next turn, the target cannot avoid the user's moves, even if the target is in the middle of a two-turn move. When this effect is started against the target, this and Mind Reader's effects end for every other Pokemon against that target. If the target leaves the field using Baton Pass, the replacement remains under this effect. If the user leaves the field using Baton Pass, this effect is restarted against the same target for the replacement. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field.
lockon.name: Lock-On
lockon.shortDesc: User's next move will not miss the target.

luckychant.name: Lucky Chant
luckychant.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members cannot be struck by a critical hit. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
luckychant.shortDesc: For 5 turns, shields user's party from critical hits.

lunardance.desc: The user faints and the Pokemon brought out to replace it has its HP and PP fully restored along with having any non-volatile status condition cured. The new Pokemon is sent out immediately and the healing happens after hazards take effect. Fails if the user is the last unfainted Pokemon in its party.
lunardance.shortDesc: User faints. Replacement is fully healed, with PP.
lunardance.name: Lunar Dance

magiccoat.desc: The user is unaffected by certain non-damaging moves directed at it and will instead use such moves against the original user. If the move targets both opposing Pokemon, the Pokemon under this effect will reflect the move only targeting the original user. The effect ends once a move is reflected or at the end of the turn. The Lightning Rod and Storm Drain Abilities redirect their respective moves before this move takes effect.
magiccoat.name: Magic Coat

magmastorm.desc: Prevents the target from switching for two to five turns (always five turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/16 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-turn. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Rapid Spin or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
magmastorm.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 2-5 turns.
magmastorm.name: Magma Storm

magnetrise.desc: For 5 turns, the user is immune to Ground-type attacks and the effects of Spikes, Toxic Spikes, and the Arena Trap Ability as long as it remains active. If the user uses Baton Pass, the replacement will gain the effect. Ingrain and Iron Ball override this move if the user is under any of their effects. Fails if the user is already under this effect or the effect of Ingrain.
magnetrise.name: Magnet Rise
magnetrise.shortDesc: For 5 turns, the user has immunity to Ground.

mefirst.desc: The user uses the move the target chose for use this turn against it, if possible, with its power multiplied by 1.5. The move must be a damaging move other than Chatter, Counter, Covet, Focus Punch, Me First, Mirror Coat, Struggle, or Thief. Fails if the target moves before the user. Ignores the target's substitute for the purpose of copying the move.
mefirst.name: Me First
mefirst.shortDesc: Copies a foe at 1.5x power. User must be faster.

metalburst.desc: Deals damage to the last opposing Pokemon to hit the user with a physical or special attack this turn equal to 1.5 times the HP lost by the user from that attack, rounded down. If that opposing Pokemon's position is no longer in use and there is another opposing Pokemon on the field, the damage is done to it instead. Only the last hit of a multi-hit attack is counted. Fails if the user was not hit by an opposing Pokemon's physical or special attack this turn, or if the user did not lose HP from the attack.
metalburst.name: Metal Burst
metalburst.shortDesc: If hit by an attack, returns 1.5x damage.

metronome.desc: A random move is selected for use, other than Assist, Chatter, Copycat, Counter, Covet, Destiny Bond, Detect, Endure, Feint, Focus Punch, Follow Me, Helping Hand, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Coat, Mirror Move, Protect, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Snatch, Struggle, Switcheroo, Thief, Trick, or any move the user already knows.
metronome.name: Metronome

mimic.desc: While the user remains active, this move is replaced by the last move used by the target. The copied move has 5 PP. Fails if the target has not made a move, if the user has Transformed, if the user already knows the move, or if the move is Chatter, Metronome, Mimic, Sketch, or Struggle.
mimic.name: Mimic
mimic.shortDesc: The last move the target used replaces this one.

minimize.desc: Raises the user's evasiveness by 1 stage. Whether or not the user's evasiveness was changed, Stomp will have its power doubled if used against the user while it is active.
minimize.name: Minimize

miracleeye.desc: As long as the target remains active, its evasiveness stat stage is ignored during accuracy checks against it if it is greater than 0, and Psychic-type attacks can hit the target if it is a Dark type.
miracleeye.name: Miracle Eye

mirrormove.desc: The user uses the last move that successfully targeted the user. The copied move is used with no specific target. Fails if no move has targeted the user, if the move was called by another move, if the move is Encore, or if the move cannot be copied by this move.
mirrormove.name: Mirror Move
mirrormove.shortDesc: User uses the target's last used move against it.

mist.name: Mist
mist.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members are protected from having their stat stages lowered by other Pokemon. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
mist.shortDesc: For 5 turns, protects user's party from stat drops.

moonlight.desc: The user restores 1/2 of its maximum HP if no weather conditions are in effect, 2/3 of its maximum HP if the weather is Sunny Day, and 1/4 of its maximum HP if the weather is Hail, Rain Dance, or Sandstorm, all rounded down.
moonlight.name: Moonlight
moonlight.shortDesc: Heals the user by a weather-dependent amount.

morningsun.desc: The user restores 1/2 of its maximum HP if no weather conditions are in effect, 2/3 of its maximum HP if the weather is Sunny Day, and 1/4 of its maximum HP if the weather is Hail, Rain Dance, or Sandstorm, all rounded down.
morningsun.name: Morning Sun
morningsun.shortDesc: Heals the user by a weather-dependent amount.

mudsport.desc: While the user is active, all Electric-type attacks used by any active Pokemon have their power halved. Fails if this effect is already active for the user. Baton Pass can be used to transfer this effect to an ally.
mudsport.shortDesc: Weakens Electric-type attacks to 1/2 their power.
mudsport.name: Mud Sport

naturepower.desc: This move calls another move for use based on the battle terrain. Tri Attack in Wi-Fi battles.
naturepower.shortDesc: Attack changes based on terrain. (Tri Attack)
naturepower.name: Nature Power

nightmare.name: Nightmare
nightmare.desc: Causes the target to lose 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn as long as it is asleep. This move does not affect the target unless it is asleep. The effect ends when the target wakes up, even if it falls asleep again in the same turn.
nightmare.shortDesc: A sleeping target is hurt by 1/4 max HP per turn.

odorsleuth.desc: As long as the target remains active, its evasiveness stat stage is ignored during accuracy checks against it if it is greater than 0, and Normal- and Fighting-type attacks can hit the target if it is a Ghost type.
odorsleuth.name: Odor Sleuth
odorsleuth.shortDesc: Fighting, Normal hit Ghost. Evasiveness ignored.

outrage.desc: The user spends two or three turns locked into this move and becomes confused at the end of the last turn of the effect if it is not already. This move targets an opposing Pokemon at random on each turn. If the user is prevented from moving, is asleep at the beginning of a turn, or the attack is not successful against the target, the effect ends without causing confusion. If this move is called by Sleep Talk, the move is used for one turn and does not confuse the user.
outrage.name: Outrage
outrage.shortDesc: Lasts 2-3 turns. Confuses the user afterwards.

payback.desc: Power doubles if the user moves after the target this turn. Switching in counts as an action.
payback.name: Payback
payback.shortDesc: Power doubles if the user moves after the target.

perishsong.name: Perish Song
perishsong.desc: Each active Pokemon receives a perish count of 4 if it doesn't already have a perish count. At the end of each turn including the turn used, the perish count of all active Pokemon lowers by 1 and Pokemon faint if the number reaches 0. The perish count is removed from Pokemon that switch out. If a Pokemon uses Baton Pass while it has a perish count, the replacement will gain the perish count and continue to count down.
perishsong.shortDesc: All active Pokemon will faint in 3 turns.

petaldance.desc: The user spends two or three turns locked into this move and becomes confused at the end of the last turn of the effect if it is not already. This move targets an opposing Pokemon at random on each turn. If the user is prevented from moving, is asleep at the beginning of a turn, or the attack is not successful against the target, the effect ends without causing confusion. If this move is called by Sleep Talk, the move is used for one turn and does not confuse the user.
petaldance.name: Petal Dance
petaldance.shortDesc: Lasts 2-3 turns. Confuses the user afterwards.

powertrick.name: Power Trick
powertrick.desc: The user swaps its Attack and Defense stats, and stat stage changes remain on their respective stats. This move can be used again to swap the stats back. If the user uses Baton Pass, the replacement will have its Attack and Defense stats swapped if the effect is active. If the user has its stats recalculated by changing forme while its stats are swapped, this effect is ignored but is still active for the purposes of Baton Pass.
powertrick.shortDesc: Switches user's Attack and Defense stats.

protect.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and doubles each time this move is successfully used, up to a maximum of 8. X resets to 1 if this move fails or if the user's last move used is not Detect, Endure, or Protect. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
protect.name: Protect
protect.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

psychup.name: Psych Up
psychup.desc: The user copies all of the target's current stat stage changes.
psychup.shortDesc: Copies the target's current stat stages.

pursuit.desc: If an opposing Pokemon switches out this turn, this move hits that Pokemon before it leaves the field, even if it was not the original target. If the user moves after an opponent using U-turn, but not Baton Pass, it will hit that opponent before it leaves the field. Power doubles and no accuracy check is done if the user hits an opponent switching out, and the user's turn is over; if an opponent faints from this, the replacement Pokemon becomes active immediately.
pursuit.name: Pursuit
pursuit.shortDesc: If a foe is switching out, hits it at 2x power.

rapidspin.desc: If this move is successful, the effects of Leech Seed and binding moves end against the user, and all hazards are removed from the user's side of the field.
rapidspin.shortDesc: Frees user from hazards, binding, Leech Seed.
rapidspin.name: Rapid Spin

recycle.desc: The user regains the item last used by a Pokemon in its current position on the field, even if that Pokemon was not the user. Fails if the user is holding an item, if no items have been used at the user's position, or if the item was lost to Covet, Knock Off, or Thief. Items thrown with Fling can be regained.
recycle.name: Recycle
recycle.shortDesc: Restores the item the user last used.

reflect.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 1/2 damage from physical attacks, or 2/3 damage if there are multiple active Pokemon on the user's side. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
reflect.name: Reflect
reflect.shortDesc: For 5 turns, physical damage to allies is halved.

reversal.desc: The power of this move is 20 if X is 43 to 48, 40 if X is 22 to 42, 80 if X is 13 to 21, 100 if X is 6 to 12, 150 if X is 2 to 5, and 200 if X is 0 or 1, where X is equal to (user's current HP * 64 / user's maximum HP), rounded down.
reversal.name: Reversal
reversal.shortDesc: More power the less HP the user has left.

roar.desc: The target is forced to switch out and be replaced with a random unfainted ally. Fails if the target is the last unfainted Pokemon in its party, if the target used Ingrain previously or has the Suction Cups Ability, or if the user's level is lower than the target's and X * (user's level + target's level) / 256 + 1 is less than or equal to (target's level / 4), rounded down, where X is a random number from 0 to 255.
roar.name: Roar
roar.shortDesc: Forces the target to switch to a random ally.

rockblast.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
rockblast.name: Rock Blast

roleplay.desc: The user's Ability changes to match the target's Ability. Fails if the user's Ability is Multitype or already matches the target, if the target's Ability is Multitype or Wonder Guard, or if the user is holding a Griseous Orb.
roleplay.name: Role Play
roleplay.shortDesc: User replaces its Ability with the target's.

safeguard.name: Safeguard
safeguard.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members cannot have non-volatile status conditions or confusion inflicted on them by other Pokemon. Pokemon on the user's side cannot become affected by Yawn but can fall asleep from its effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Defog. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
safeguard.shortDesc: For 5 turns, protects user's party from status.

sandtomb.desc: Prevents the target from switching for two to five turns (always five turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/16 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-turn. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Rapid Spin or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
sandtomb.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 2-5 turns.
sandtomb.name: Sand Tomb

scaryface.name: Scary Face
scaryface.desc: Lowers the target's Speed by 2 stages.

secretpower.desc: Has a 30% chance to cause a secondary effect on the target based on the battle terrain. Causes paralysis on the regular Wi-Fi terrain.
secretpower.shortDesc: Effect varies with terrain. (30% paralysis chance)
secretpower.name: Secret Power

sketch.desc: This move is permanently replaced by the last move used by the target. The copied move has the maximum PP for that move. Fails if the target has not made a move, if the user has Transformed, or if the move is Chatter, Sketch, Struggle, or any move the user knows.
sketch.name: Sketch
sketch.shortDesc: Permanently copies the last move target used.

skillswap.desc: The user swaps its Ability with the target's Ability. Fails if either the user or the target's Ability is Multitype or Wonder Guard, if both have the same Ability, or if either is holding a Griseous Orb.
skillswap.name: Skill Swap
skillswap.shortDesc: The user and the target trade Abilities.

sleeptalk.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Bide, Chatter, Copycat, Focus Punch, Me First, Metronome, Mirror Move, Sleep Talk, Uproar, or any two-turn move.
sleeptalk.name: Sleep Talk
sleeptalk.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

snatch.desc: If another Pokemon uses certain non-damaging moves this turn, the user steals that move to use itself. If multiple Pokemon use this move this turn, the applicable moves are stolen by each of those Pokemon in turn order, and only the last user in turn order will gain the effects.
snatch.name: Snatch
snatch.shortDesc: User steals certain support moves to use itself.

snore.name: Snore
snore.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch. Fails if the user is not asleep.
snore.shortDesc: User must be asleep. 30% chance to flinch target.

spikes.desc: Sets up a hazard on the opposing side of the field, damaging each opposing Pokemon that switches in, unless it is a Flying-type Pokemon or has the Levitate Ability. Can be used up to three times before failing. Opponents lose 1/8 of their maximum HP with one layer, 1/6 of their maximum HP with two layers, and 1/4 of their maximum HP with three layers, all rounded down. Can be removed from the opposing side if any opposing Pokemon uses Rapid Spin successfully, or is hit by Defog.
spikes.name: Spikes
spikes.shortDesc: Hurts grounded foes on switch-in. Max 3 layers.

spite.name: Spite
spite.desc: Causes the target's last move used to lose 4 PP. Fails if the target has not made a move, if the move has 0 PP, or if it no longer knows the move.
spite.shortDesc: Lowers the PP of the target's last move by 4.

stealthrock.desc: Sets up a hazard on the opposing side of the field, damaging each opposing Pokemon that switches in. Fails if the effect is already active on the opposing side. Foes lose 1/32, 1/16, 1/8, 1/4, or 1/2 of their maximum HP, rounded down, based on their weakness to the Rock type; 0.25x, 0.5x, neutral, 2x, or 4x, respectively. Can be removed from the opposing side if any opposing Pokemon uses Rapid Spin successfully, or is hit by Defog.
stealthrock.name: Stealth Rock
stealthrock.shortDesc: Hurts foes on switch-in. Factors Rock weakness.

struggle.desc: Deals typeless damage to a random opposing Pokemon. If this move was successful, the user loses 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and the Rock Head Ability does not prevent this. This move is automatically used if none of the user's known moves can be selected.
struggle.name: Struggle
struggle.shortDesc: User loses 1/4 of its max HP.

substitute.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokemon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokemon. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
substitute.name: Substitute
substitute.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

suckerpunch.desc: Fails if the target did not select a physical or special attack for use this turn, or if the target moves before the user.
suckerpunch.name: Sucker Punch
suckerpunch.shortDesc: Usually goes first. Fails if target is not attacking.

switcheroo.desc: The user swaps its held item with the target's held item. Fails if either the user or the target is holding a Mail or Griseous Orb, if neither is holding an item, if either has the Multitype Ability, if either is under the effect of Knock Off, or if the target has the Sticky Hold Ability.
switcheroo.name: Switcheroo
switcheroo.shortDesc: User switches its held item with the target's.

synthesis.desc: The user restores 1/2 of its maximum HP if no weather conditions are in effect, 2/3 of its maximum HP if the weather is Sunny Day, and 1/4 of its maximum HP if the weather is Hail, Rain Dance, or Sandstorm, all rounded down.
synthesis.name: Synthesis
synthesis.shortDesc: Heals the user by a weather-dependent amount.

tailglow.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack by 2 stages.
tailglow.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk by 2.
tailglow.name: Tail Glow

tailwind.desc: For 3 turns, the user and its party members have their Speed doubled. Fails if this move is already in effect for the user's side.
tailwind.shortDesc: For 3 turns, allies' Speed is doubled.
tailwind.name: Tailwind

taunt.desc: For 3 to 5 turns, prevents the target from using non-damaging moves.
taunt.shortDesc: For 3-5 turns, the target can't use status moves.
taunt.name: Taunt

thrash.desc: The user spends two or three turns locked into this move and becomes confused at the end of the last turn of the effect if it is not already. This move targets an opposing Pokemon at random on each turn. If the user is prevented from moving, is asleep at the beginning of a turn, or the attack is not successful against the target, the effect ends without causing confusion. If this move is called by Sleep Talk, the move is used for one turn and does not confuse the user.
thrash.name: Thrash
thrash.shortDesc: Lasts 2-3 turns. Confuses the user afterwards.

torment.name: Torment
torment.desc: Prevents the target from selecting the same move for use two turns in a row. This effect ends when the target is no longer active.
torment.shortDesc: Target can't select the same move twice in a row.

toxicspikes.desc: Sets up a hazard on the opposing side of the field, poisoning each opposing Pokemon that switches in, unless it is a Flying-type Pokemon or has the Levitate Ability. Can be used up to two times before failing. Opposing Pokemon become poisoned with one layer and badly poisoned with two layers. Can be removed from the opposing side if any opposing Pokemon uses Rapid Spin successfully, is hit by Defog, or a grounded Poison-type Pokemon switches in. Safeguard prevents the opposing party from being poisoned on switch-in, as well as switching in with a substitute.
toxicspikes.name: Toxic Spikes
toxicspikes.shortDesc: Poisons grounded foes on switch-in. Max 2 layers.

transform.desc: The user transforms into the target. The target's current stats, stat stages, types, moves, Ability, weight, IVs, species, and sprite are copied. The user's level and HP remain the same and each copied move receives only 5 PP. This move fails if the target has transformed.
transform.name: Transform
transform.shortDesc: Copies target's stats, moves, types, and Ability.

trick.desc: The user swaps its held item with the target's held item. Fails if either the user or the target is holding a Mail or Griseous Orb, if neither is holding an item, if either has the Multitype Ability, if either is under the effect of Knock Off, or if the target has the Sticky Hold Ability.
trick.name: Trick
trick.shortDesc: User switches its held item with the target's.

trickroom.desc: For 5 turns, all active Pokemon with lower Speed will move before those with higher Speed, within their priority brackets. If this move is used during the effect, the effect ends.
trickroom.name: Trick Room
trickroom.shortDesc: Goes last. For 5 turns, turn order is reversed.

uproar.desc: The user spends three to six turns locked into this move. This move targets an opponent at random on each turn. During effect, no active Pokemon can fall asleep by any means, and Pokemon that are already asleep wake up as their turn starts or at the end of each turn, including the last one. If the user is prevented from moving or the attack is not successful against the target during one of the turns, the effect ends.
uproar.shortDesc: Lasts 3-6 turns. Active Pokemon cannot sleep.
uproar.name: Uproar

volttackle.desc: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target. If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/3 the HP lost by the target, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
volttackle.shortDesc: Has 1/3 recoil. 10% chance to paralyze target.
volttackle.name: Volt Tackle

watersport.desc: While the user is active, all Fire-type attacks used by any active Pokemon have their power halved. Fails if this effect is already active for the user. Baton Pass can be used to transfer this effect to an ally.
watersport.shortDesc: Weakens Fire-type attacks to 1/2 their power.
watersport.name: Water Sport

whirlpool.desc: Prevents the target from switching for two to five turns (always five turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/16 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-turn. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Rapid Spin or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
whirlpool.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 2-5 turns.
whirlpool.name: Whirlpool

whirlwind.desc: The target is forced to switch out and be replaced with a random unfainted ally. Fails if the target is the last unfainted Pokemon in its party, if the target used Ingrain previously or has the Suction Cups Ability, or if the user's level is lower than the target's and X * (user's level + target's level) / 256 + 1 is less than or equal to (target's level / 4), rounded down, where X is a random number from 0 to 255.
whirlwind.name: Whirlwind
whirlwind.shortDesc: Forces the target to switch to a random ally.

wish.desc: At the end of the next turn, the Pokemon at the user's position has 1/2 of its maximum HP restored to it, rounded down. Fails if this move is already in effect for the user's position.
wish.shortDesc: Next turn, heals 50% of the recipient's max HP.
wish.name: Wish

woodhammer.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/3 the HP lost by the target, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
woodhammer.name: Wood Hammer

worryseed.desc: Causes the target's Ability to become Insomnia. Fails if the target's Ability is Multitype or Truant, or if the target is holding a Griseous Orb.
worryseed.name: Worry Seed

wrap.desc: Prevents the target from switching for two to five turns (always five turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/16 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-turn. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Rapid Spin or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
wrap.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 2-5 turns.
wrap.name: Wrap

wringout.desc: Power is equal to 120 * (target's current HP / target's maximum HP) + 1, rounded down.
wringout.name: Wring Out
wringout.shortDesc: More power the more HP the target has left.

yawn.name: Yawn
yawn.desc: Causes the target to fall asleep at the end of the next turn. Fails when used if the target cannot fall asleep or if it already has a non-volatile status condition. At the end of the next turn, if the target is still active, does not have a non-volatile status condition, and can fall asleep, it falls asleep. If the target becomes affected, this effect cannot be prevented by Safeguard or a substitute, or by falling asleep and waking up during the effect.
yawn.shortDesc: Puts the target to sleep after 1 turn.

absorb.desc: The user recovers 1/2 the HP lost by the target, rounded down. If Big Root is held by the user, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded down.
absorb.name: Absorb
absorb.shortDesc: User recovers 50% of the damage dealt.

armthrust.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
armthrust.name: Arm Thrust

assist.desc: A random move among those known by the user's party members is selected for use. Does not select Assist, Chatter, Copycat, Counter, Covet, Destiny Bond, Detect, Endure, Feint, Focus Punch, Follow Me, Helping Hand, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Coat, Mirror Move, Protect, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Snatch, Struggle, Switcheroo, Thief, or Trick.
assist.name: Assist
assist.shortDesc: Uses a random move known by a team member.

assurance.desc: Power doubles if the target has already taken damage this turn.
assurance.name: Assurance
assurance.shortDesc: Power doubles if target was damaged this turn.

avalanche.desc: Power doubles if the user was hit by a Pokemon in the target's position this turn.
avalanche.name: Avalanche
avalanche.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is damaged by the target.

barrage.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
barrage.name: Barrage

block.desc: Prevents the target from switching out. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-turn. If the target leaves the field using Baton Pass, the replacement will remain trapped. The effect ends if the user leaves the field, unless it uses Baton Pass, in which case the target will remain trapped.
block.name: Block
block.shortDesc: Prevents the target from switching out.

bonemerang.desc: Hits twice. If the first hit breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the second hit. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
bonemerang.name: Bonemerang

bounce.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. On the first turn, the user avoids all attacks other than Gust, Sky Uppercut, Thunder, and Twister, and Gust and Twister have doubled power when used against it. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
bounce.name: Bounce

brickbreak.desc: If this attack does not miss and whether or not the target is immune, the effects of Reflect and Light Screen end for the target's side of the field before damage is calculated.
brickbreak.shortDesc: Destroys screens, even if the target is immune.
brickbreak.name: Brick Break

bugbite.desc: The user steals the target's held Berry if it is holding one and eats it immediately, gaining its effects unless the user's item is being ignored. Items lost to this move can be regained with Recycle.
bugbite.name: Bug Bite
bugbite.shortDesc: User steals and eats the target's Berry.

cometpunch.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
cometpunch.name: Comet Punch

conversion2.desc: The user's type changes to match a type that resists or is immune to the type of the last move used against the user, if it was successful against the user, but not either of its current types. The determined type of the move is used rather than the original type. Fails if the last move used against the user was not successful, if the user has the Multitype Ability, or if this move would only be able to select one of the user's current types.
conversion2.shortDesc: User's type changes to resist last move against it.
conversion2.name: Conversion 2

copycat.desc: The user uses the last move used by any Pokemon, including itself. Fails if no move has been used, or if the last move used was Assist, Chatter, Copycat, Counter, Covet, Destiny Bond, Detect, Endure, Feint, Focus Punch, Follow Me, Helping Hand, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Coat, Mirror Move, Protect, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Snatch, Struggle, Switcheroo, Thief, or Trick.
copycat.name: Copycat
copycat.shortDesc: Uses the last move used in the battle.

counter.desc: Deals damage to the last opposing Pokemon to hit the user with a physical attack this turn equal to twice the HP lost by the user from that attack. If that opposing Pokemon's position is no longer in use and there is another opposing Pokemon on the field, the damage is done to it instead. Only the last hit of a multi-hit attack is counted. Fails if the user was not hit by an opposing Pokemon's physical attack this turn, or if the user did not lose HP from the attack.
counter.name: Counter
counter.shortDesc: If hit by physical attack, returns double damage.

dig.desc: This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. On the first turn, the user avoids all attacks other than Earthquake and Magnitude, which have doubled power when used against it, and is also unaffected by weather. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
dig.name: Dig

dive.desc: This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. On the first turn, the user avoids all attacks other than Surf and Whirlpool, which have doubled power when used against it, and is also unaffected by weather. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
dive.name: Dive

doublehit.desc: Hits twice. If the first hit breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the second hit. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
doublehit.name: Double Hit

doublekick.desc: Hits twice. If the first hit breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the second hit. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
doublekick.name: Double Kick

doubleslap.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
doubleslap.name: Double Slap

earthquake.desc: Power doubles if the target is using Dig.
earthquake.shortDesc: Hits adjacent Pokemon. Power doubles on Dig.
earthquake.name: Earthquake

endure.desc: The user will survive attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn with at least 1 HP. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and doubles each time this move is successfully used, up to a maximum of 8. X resets to 1 if this move fails or if the user's last move used is not Detect, Endure, or Protect. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
endure.name: Endure
endure.shortDesc: User survives attacks this turn with at least 1 HP.

explosion.desc: The user faints after using this move, unless this move has no target. The target's Defense is halved during damage calculation. This move is prevented from executing if any active Pokemon has the Damp Ability.
explosion.shortDesc: Target's Def halved during damage. User faints.
explosion.name: Explosion

firefang.desc: Has a 10% chance to burn the target and a 10% chance to make it flinch. This move can hit Pokemon with the Wonder Guard Ability regardless of their typing.
firefang.name: Fire Fang
firefang.shortDesc: 10% chance to burn. 10% chance to flinch.

fling.desc: The power of this move is based on the user's held item. The held item is lost and it activates for the target if applicable. If the target avoids this move by protecting itself, the user's held item is still lost. The user can regain a thrown item with Recycle. Fails if the user has no held item, if the held item cannot be thrown, or if the user is under the effect of Embargo.
fling.name: Fling
fling.shortDesc: Flings the user's item at the target. Power varies.

fly.desc: This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. On the first turn, the user avoids all attacks other than Gust, Sky Uppercut, Thunder, and Twister, and Gust and Twister have doubled power when used against it. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
fly.name: Fly
fly.shortDesc: Flies up on first turn, then strikes the next turn.

followme.desc: Until the end of the turn, all single-target attacks from the opposing side are redirected to the user. Such attacks are redirected to the user before they can be reflected by Magic Coat, or drawn in by the Lightning Rod or Storm Drain Abilities. This effect remains active even if the user leaves the field. Fails if it is not a Double Battle.
followme.name: Follow Me
followme.shortDesc: The foes' moves target the user on the turn used.

furyattack.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
furyattack.name: Fury Attack

furyswipes.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 3/8 chance to hit two or three times, and a 1/8 chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times. If the target has a Focus Sash and had full HP when this move started, it will not be knocked out regardless of the number of hits.
furyswipes.name: Fury Swipes

gust.desc: Power doubles if the target is using Bounce or Fly.
gust.shortDesc: Power doubles during Bounce and Fly.
gust.name: Gust

hail.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Hail. At the end of each turn except the last, all active Pokemon lose 1/16 of their maximum HP, rounded down, unless they are an Ice type or have the Ice Body, Magic Guard, or Snow Cloak Abilities. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Icy Rock. Fails if the current weather is Hail.
hail.name: Hail

headsmash.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/2 the HP lost by the target, rounded down, but not less than 1 HP.
headsmash.name: Head Smash

healorder.desc: The user restores 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded down.
healorder.name: Heal Order
healorder.shortDesc: Heals the user by 50% of its max HP.

leechlife.desc: The user recovers 1/2 the HP lost by the target, rounded down. If Big Root is held by the user, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded down.
leechlife.name: Leech Life
leechlife.shortDesc: User recovers 50% of the damage dealt.

magnitude.desc: The power of this move varies. 5% chances for 10 and 150 power, 10% chances for 30 and 110 power, 20% chances for 50 and 90 power, and 30% chance for 70 power. Power doubles if the target is using Dig.
magnitude.name: Magnitude
